<TEXT>
at 99 the father of public relations 
is still promoting clients and himself 
edward bernays showed signs of outlasting his listeners tuesday 
as he made a whirlwind tour of the university of massachusetts 
at 99 i work 12 hours a day just as i did before and if a 
client comes in we make no bones about it he pays 1000 an 
hour for advice bernays said during three hours of gab about his 
career promoting such clients as sigmund freud enrico caruso 
vaslav nijinsky calvin coolidge and other presidents 
in 1923 bernays taught the first college course in public 
relations at new york university his 1923 book crystallizing 
public opinion is considered the bible of the business 
bernays who lives in cambridge dismissed retirement at age 65 
as a cockeyed idea he said his theory that work keeps him 
young was supported during a doctors visit at 94 when tests 
showed he had the body of a 62yearold 
he made the 16 tests again when i was 95 and i found i was 
61 bernays said 
colleagues marvel at his ability to captivate the public and his 
mastery of getting clients stories into newsprint and onto 
broadcasting airwaves 
he is absolutely indefatigable said scott m cutlip dean 
emeritus at the university of georgia and coauthor of a widely 
used public relations text 
cutlip credited bernays with establishing twoway communication 
between clients and news media rather than simply distributing 
news releases or waiting for reporters to come to the client 
another of his principles involves staging the kind of 
demonstrations that have since become the norm worldwide 
actions speak louder than words bernays said giving as an 
example his efforts on behalf of the tobacco industry decades ago 
to make it acceptable for women to smoke in public 
he said he helped engineer the change in attitudes with the help 
of debutante friends who lit cigarettes as socalled torches of 
freedom during easter day parades 
about 30 years later when the surgeon general revealed the 
hazards of smoking bernays said he campaigned to get tobacco 
advertising off the airwaves in atonement 
his contact with freud a maternal uncle resulted in the 
american publication of introductory lectures in 
psychoanalysis which previously had been published only in 
europe 
and there were efforts to revamp coolidges sourpuss image 
trying to erase the image created by the frequent sarcastic 
comment that calvin coolidge was weaned on a pickle bernays 
said he promoted a white house breakfast visit by a group of 
actors who were considered slightly raffish in those days 
newspapers all over the country carried the story 
i recall the new york times they had a story that had about 
five subheads and the fourth headline in the new york times 
was president nearly laughed bernays said 
