the influx of soviet jewish immigrants is 
beginning to hit israelis in their paychecks and is showing signs 
of straining prime minister yitzhak shamirs fragile coalition 
government 
while public support remains generally high the sheer magnitude 
of the task ahead housing employing and educating 1000 
newcomers a day is becoming increasingly daunting 
the impact of the immigration flood 150000 so far this year 
an estimated 1 million by the end of 1992 is now felt throughout 
this country of about 44 million people 
some people are voicing doubts about whether israel can take the 
strain 
there is an atmosphere of panic among the politicians 
absorbing an immigration wave of the scope we are now facing is 
a mission beyond israels capability warned the respected 
haaretz newspaper 
but to do anything to stem the flow would negate israels very 
reason for existing as haaretz pointed out this is a zionist 
state taking in jews is its aim and essence so nobody dares to 
say it out loud 
the 1991 state budget for the first time allocates more to 
immigrant absorption than to defense the military lost its fight 
for a budget increase and had to cancel an order for two 
germanbuilt submarines 
