reap financial and political capital while seeking to shatter 
the soviet state 
the formation of some ultraradical political movements is not 
at all spontaneous but it is deliberate and well thought out some 
of them have ample material and moral support from abroad he 
said 
destructive elements take the path of organizing what in 
effect is economic sabotage aggravating the situation in the 
consumer market said kryuchkov 
he said the kgb would work to fight economic sabotage and 
prevent foreign products from being illegally diverted 
any attempts to hinder these activities will be resolutely 
stopped by all means that are at the disposal of the kgb he 
said 
