in arab east jerusalem police fired tear gas and rubber bullets 
in several locations to disperse stonethrowers police arrested 
six palestinians and closed two schools 
the fatal clash occurred along the highway that links the 
occupied west bank with the tel aviv area and is frequently used by 
jewish settlers 
about 200 students from the arab village of biddiya threw stones 
at israeli cars during a demonstration marking the anniversary of 
the founding of a radical plo faction an arab reporter said 
settlers and soldiers fired at the protesters and one bullet 
struck ahlam abed in the head the report said her body was taken 
to ittihad hospital in the west bank town of nablus 
her death brought to 778 the number of palestinians killed by 
israelis since the start of the uprising three years ago at least 
316 other palestinians have been killed by fellow arabs most on 
suspicion of helping israel fiftyfour israelis also have died in 
the violence 
a 16yearold palestinian from the west bank town of tulkarem 
was reported in serious but stable condition wednesday after he was 
shot in the head by a rubber bullet during clashes with the army 
tuesday 
in east jerusalem dozens of palestinians threw stones and glue 
containers at police in the main shopping street police responded 
with tear gas and rubber bullets and arrested five 
in the nearby wadi joz neighborhood two israelis were hurt when 
their car overturned after the driver lost control of the vehicle 
when it was stoned police said 
