here are the resignation letter from secretary 
of education lauro f cavazos and president bushs reply both 
dated dec 12 
dear mr president 
i lauro f cavazos hereby resign as united states secretary of 
education effective close of business dec 15 1990 
i appreciate the opportunity to work with the administration in 
helping to further its goals toward excellence in education i am 
especially proud of the contributions i was able to make in 
expanding choice in education promoting the executive order on 
excellence in education for hispanic americans and raising 
awareness of the growing diversity of americas student population 
i have only the greatest expectations and highest hopes that 
each child in america will be educated to his or her fullest 
potential 
respectfully 
lauro f cavazos 
 
dear larry 
with deep regret i accept your letter of resignation for more 
than two years and under two presidents you have distinguished 
yourself through your devotion to improving the education of our 
nations children 
with your help and guidance we assembled the 50 state governors 
in charlottesville for a historic education summit there we 
established a consensus for a set of national education goals 
which today are the driving force behind our education agenda your 
tireless promotion and pursuit of these goals has set us on a path 
to educational excellence through the end of the decade 
i was particularly proud larry to stand with you last 
september to announce an executive order on educational excellence 
for hispanic americans based on the findings of the task force you 
led hispanic americans in every community are indebted to you for 
the inspired leadership you have provided 
barbara and i will always be grateful for the sincerity 
diligence and care you brought to the office of the secretary on 
behalf of students parents and teachers across the nation let me 
thank you for your dedicated service 
sincerely 
george bush 
</TEXT>
