secretary of state james a baker iii 
hopes to meet with foreign ministers of the other permanent 
security council members in europe this month to reassure iraq it 
wont be attacked if it withdraws from kuwait by jan 15 diplomats 
said today 
but the foreign ministers will also tell iraqi president saddam 
hussein that they will not accept a partial withdrawal thus 
forestalling any idea that he could hang on to two islands that 
control access to the shattalarab waterway or part of an oil 
field straddling the iraqkuwait border 
soviet foreign minister eduard a shevardnadze who is in 
