shamir 
he voiced us concerns about treatment of palestinians living 
under israeli occupation said assistant secretary of state john 
kelly but he did not bring up the slaying of 17 palestinians by 
israeli police during an october riot at a jerusalem holy site 
shamir asked bush for help possibly in the form of loan 
guarantees in absorbing soviet jews who are coming to israel the 
president said he would think about it 
