other leading groups in the socalled education establishment 
cavazos had campaigned for efforts to give parents more choice 
over what public school their child attends 
bush praised cavazos for his help and guidance in arranging 
last years education summit with the nations governors at 
charlottesville va which produced a set of education goals for 
elevating standards in americas schools 
those goals are the driving force behind our education 
agenda said bush your tireless promotion and pursuit of these 
goals has set us on a path to educational excellence through the 
end of the decade 
cavazos was only the fourth person to be secretary of education 
the post was created when education was elevated to cabinet status 
in 1980 during the carter administration 
labor secretary elizabeth dole announced her resignation in 
october the first of bushs cabinet to resign 
cavazos had earned a bachelors degree in zoology and a masters 
degree in cytology at the same school then known as texas 
technological college before getting a doctorate in physiology 
from iowa state university in 1954 
he first taught as an instructor of anatomy and later as an 
associate professor at the medical college of virginia in 
richmond later he was dean of the school of medicine at tufts 
university in medford mass 
in 1980 he became the first alumnus and the first hispanic to 
be named president of texas tech 
cavazos father was a cattle foreman at the king ranch in texas 
cavazos has two brothers who also attended texas tech and went on 
to successful careers bobby cavazos was an allamerican running 
back in college afterward he ran his own ranch brother dick 
became a fourstar army general 
the retiring education secretary and his wife peggy ann have 
10 children seven of them have degrees from texas tech 
