70yearold defense minister gen abdeljabbar khalil shanshal 
was retiring because of his age he held the post for just over a 
year 
the radio said the new defense minister is maj gen saadi tuma 
abbas the inspectorgeneral of the armed forces and a former 
deputy chief of staff 
abbas who is in his fifties was a hero of the 198088 war with 
iran he commanded the defense of basra against the iranians whose 
attacking armies came within a few miles of the southern port city 
he was the strategist behind the formidable defensive lines 
built to protect basra from iranian human wave assaults the 
iraqis who have an estimated 450000 troops in and around kuwait 
have built similar fortifications around kuwait 
abbas later commanded troops involved in heavy fighting with the 
iranians in the southern iraq theater the main battleground in 
that conflict 
shanshals dismissal comes just over a month before the un 
security councils jan 15 deadline for him to quit kuwait or face 
a possible military assault 
some analysts said that by appointing abbas saddam was 
underscoring readiness to go to war 
us officials have reported a steady buildup of iraqi forces in 
