against any further iraqi aggression 
in the early days of the crisis an undetermined number of 
americans managed to escape many by driving across the the desert 
to remote border crossings 
early on foreign governments were reluctant to refer to the 
trapped foreigners as hostages fearing that would inflame the 
situation at a time when their release might still be arranged 
