the antiiraq alliance the us government saw saddams piecemeal 
release of the hostages as a bid to divide the coalition 
on nov 18 iraq offered to release all the hostages in batches 
over a threemonth period extending from christmas to march 25 if 
nothing happened to mar the atmosphere of peace that was seen 
by us officials as an effort by saddam to drag out the process 
during a likely time frame for any attack 
