<TEXT>
a commission has been chosen to enforce a 
presidential order to crack down on pornography the soviet culture 
minister said wednesday but he promised it wont be a new 
inquisition 
president mikhail s gorbachev this month ordered culture 
minister nikolai gubenko to form the committee to protect public 
morality from pornography 
gubenko said the committee consists of 30 people and includes 
chiefs of creative unions state committees public organizations 
representatives of religious movements and prominent cultural 
figures the tass news agency reported 
he said it will begin work after its membership is completed 
next week 
in his order gorbachev cited public concern about the spread of 
erotic photos and videos as well as pseudomedical literature 
gorbachevs policy of glasnost or openness and a new law on 
the press has virtually ended censorship allowed democratic debate 
to flower and let many new people into the publishing business but 
many soviets find offensive some of the new private publishers 
choice of material 
softcore erotica has been flourishing in the traditionally 
puritan soviet union 
pinupstyle posters and calendrs of naked women are sold openly 
near the entrances of many moscow subway stations sometimes tacked 
up in full view of commuters sex manuals are sold on city streets 
popular movies such as little vera and interdevochka 
intergirl have featured some nudity and explicit scenes although 
they were comparatively mild by western standards soviet 
television also broadcasts movies from other countries that are 
somewhat more explicit than those shown on american tv 
tass headlined its story on the commissions meeting wednesday 
soviet union prepares to clamp down on sleaze 
its report said the emancipation of public morals and the 
freedom of commercial activities have had a negative impact on the 
moral health of soviet society 
it is necessary to stop the squall of pornography 
pseudomedical literature erotic films and propaganda of violence 
and cruelty 
the agency said the commission will study the experience of 
countries such as denmark sweden france the united states and 
germany in fighting pornography 
in order to solve this problem we wont resort to tough 
measures for instance like in china tass quoted gubenko as 
saying china this year launched a widespread campaign that meted 
out harsh penalties for those convicted of disseminating 
pornography 
we have no plan to launch a new inquisition here he said 
gubenko told soviet tv that commission priorities will be to 
work out mechanisms to regulate processes in the framework of 
culturally traditional and religious coloring of various 
territories of our country 
asked if the commission will focus on barring certain materials 
gubenko replied not at all otherwise we would cut our own 
throat as far as the freedom of information is concerned 
an adult person who has access to all kinds of information 
its their personal affair he said we are talking about the 
younger generation which we must protect from the danger of 
destroying its psyche 
gubenko said the soviet parliament and the president not his 
commission probably would be the final authority 
