horrible religion its a christian heresy and we deal with our 
heretics in different ways 
asked if his views affected his work on the scrolls which trace 
the evolution of modern judaism strugnell said i dont when 
im working on a qumran area where scrolls were found text think 
how stupid and wrong the jews were im concerned with trying to 
find out what a document is saying in its context 
strugnell insisted he had nothing against jews saying i dont 
love or hate jews more than i love or hate anybody else 
the new york times on wednesday quoted frank moore cross 
another harvard scholar working on the scrolls as saying the 
interview certainly contributed to strugnells dismissal 
ulrich who was appointed as one of three editors to replace 
strugnell called the remarks highly and inflammatorily 
antisemitic 
but ulrich also said he doesnt believe strugnell meant what he 
said 
i have known john for 20 years and ive never heard him say 
anything like that ulrich said 
strugnell 60 who has been editor since 1987 has been 
unavailable for comment harvard spokesman peter costa said he was 
in an unidentified hospital for treatment of an undisclosed 
illness 
ulrich however said strugnell told him sunday he does not 
see it as all over and done with 
the dead sea scrolls were discovered by bedouin shepherds in 
1947 in a cave in what is now the israelioccupied west bank they 
contain some of the earliest known biblical texts including copies 
of the old testament dating to the second and third century bc 
they are kept at the rockefeller museum in jerusalem 
scholars say the 800 scrolls shed light on the life of the 
essenes an ancient sect of jews as well as the roots of early 
christianity 
strugnell has been criticized for the scholars slow pace in 
publishing the scrolls some of which were found in fragments as 
small as a dime 
its been very clear for awhile that john has not been moving 
quickly enough said new york university professor larry 
schiffman a dead sea scrolls scholar who is not on the editing 
team 
schiffman said wednesday poor management was the real reason 
behind strugnells dismissal although the antijewish remarks 
didnt help 
hershel shanks editor of biblical archaeology review dismissed 
the explanation that strugnell was fired for health problems 
you dont fire a man because hes ill shanks said its 
because they dont want to be associated with an antisemite 
