6yearolds an education department official said wednesday 
critics said the tests might not be reliable or useful for the 
younger children 
the special study panel on education indicators concluded two 
days of meetings in bethesda md after developing a draft report 
said john ralph study director 
the panel formed a year ago to suggest to congress how to 
update indicators that are used to measure education quality 
operates within the national center for education statistics part 
of the education department 
the most controversial item under consideration by the 19member 
group is the proposal to assess a sampling of 6yearolds to 
determine how prepared they are to enter school and to assess 
3yearolds so educators can identify and measure things that put 
them at risk of failure in school 
the proposal was first reported by the trade publication 
education daily 
the group will meet again early next year to refine its report 
before submitting it to congress in may 
were extremely concerned about the plan for a nationwide 
assessment of 3yearolds said barbara willer of the national 
association for the education of young children 
the study group she said appears to be unaware of the problems 
of testing young children she said the items they want to assess 
are virtually impossible to assess all of these are emerging 
areas for testing in 3yearolds and to test them doesnt seem 
to be a wise use of money 
