of any real good assessments or valid tests for 3yearolds that 
can be given to large samples of students 
the sampling approach suggested by the study group is similar to 
that used by the national assessment popularly called the 
nations report card because it measures what students know in 
grades four eight and 12 and what skills they possess 
society can undertake early preventive measures that minimize 
the deficits these children might carry with them into their 
subsequent educational experiences said the study groups draft 
report 
the early testing can help determine the sources of 
educational inequities near their roots rather than after children 
have already spent time in elementary school 
separate information may also be useful for the subgroups of 
children that differ in the number of parents living in the 
household maternal education levels preschoolkindergarten 
experiences and geographic regions said the report 
it said testing of 3yearolds and 6yearolds must measure 
