cents of every tax dollar goes to waste 
pollsters and republican political consultants warned gop 
governors here that the budget and tax dilemma most states face is 
likely to deepen before the next elections they urged the 
executives to start dealing with it early to ease the sting before 
the 1992 campaign season 
theres no place for a governor to hide said richard 
wirthlin who conducts polls for the white house he said the 
governors should shape clear strategies for handling the budget 
squeeze and the tax issue and tell their constituents about it 
wirthlin said a poll his organization conducted in september 
found that the average american believes that local state and 
federal governments waste 49 cents of every dollar taxpayers send 
them 
eightytwo percent of the people think government wastes the 
money it gets wirthlin said 
thats a presumption as a governor that youve got to take on 
and take on very directly he told the republican governors 
conference this week 
the peril in taxes hardly came as a surprise to the governors 
fourteen states switched party control in gubernatorial elections 
this year in almost every case when incumbents or their parties 
lost taxes were a factor 
surveys by wirthlin after the nov 6 elections showed that among 
people who made their choice on the basis of a single issue 9 
