the daihatsu charade is a practical car that has special appeal 
for budgetminded households environmentalists qualityconscious 
consumers and anyone who frets over the safety of small cars 
built by the 83yearold japanese manufacturer daihatsu motor 
co the charade is a relative newcomer to the united states it 
arrived in the 1988 model year and sales thus far have totaled only 
about 36500 
the little car has gained attention in a short time however 
the charade is among the most fuelefficient cars sold in the 
united states which admirers say makes it both economical and 
cleaner than many competitors the consumer group public citizen 
named it one of the top environmentally sensitive vehicles in the 
country on the basis of fuel economy 
in october the automotive marketing research firm jd power 
and associates reported that the charade received more owner 
recommendations per vehicle than any other nameplate except acura 
in powers 1990 customer satisfaction survey 
and last year the charade ranked top in its class in 
crashworthiness tests by the national highway traffic safety 
administration 
the car protects its owners wallets pretty well too the base 
price of 6597 is less than half that of the average car and fuel 
economy in mixed cityhighway driving is over 40 miles per gallon 
the thriftiness is squeezed out of a threecylinder 1liter 
engine that develops only 53 horsepower pickup suffers with an 
engine that small and daihatsu should consider a tachometer to 
help drivers make their way through the fivespeed manual 
transmission 
the 1990 hatchback offered for testing got good marks for 
maneuverability however thanks to its small size 1449 inches 
long and rack and pinion steering 
the exterior was simple a 3door hatchback design similar to 
the ford festiva and dodge colt there wasnt even molding on the 
sides of the charade body but fit and finish were admirable 
the interior was spartan and fairly loud from engine and road 
noise though without rattles there were no side map pockets on 
the doors but there was a coin holder beneath the parking brake 
lever and the rear seat was fairly well cushioned another nice 
touch the ventilation fan did a good job of moving air around 
inside 
rear legroom was surprisingly good when the front seats were 
moved up a ways though my knees touched the seatbacks when they 
were moved all the way back on their tracks and reclined slightly 
daihatsu says there is 318 inches of rear legroom in the car 
nearly equal to the 319 inches in the new toyota tercel which is 
nearly 17 inches longer on the outside 
there was a handy rear tray to help cover items stowed in the 
hatchback area rear carpeting in the hatchback area was thin and 
had a tendency to bunch up behind the rear seat the seat by the 
way folds down for additional cargo space 
the car meets its goal of providing basic transportation and is 
a worthy competitor in the crowded subcompact field which includes 
the tercel starting at 6488 the nissan sentra starting at 
7999 and the honda civic starting at more than 6600 
daihatsu says on average its buyers are about 30 have some 
college education and an annual household income of between 25000 
and 40000 
the 235 daihatsu dealers in 22 states are still selling 1990 
models the company says it does not expect 1991 models to arrive 
in showrooms until february prices of the 1991 models have not 
been announced 
consumer reports did not have an owner trouble report for the 
charade 
