<TEXT>
thomas nast elevated american political 
cartooning out of the realm of whimsy in the late 19th century 
shocking the public with his scathing portrayals of politicians and 
other public figures 
his drawings were credited with electing one presidential 
candidate and blamed for contributing to the death of another 
he held new york citys political machine up to ridicule across 
the nation and he left us several enduring symbols the 
starsandstripessuited uncle sam the democratic party donkey 
the republican elephant the tammany hall tiger and the rotund 
redjowled image of santa claus 
in the 150th year since his birth nast and his work are the 
subjects of renewed interest his christmas scenes are becoming 
more popular a biography is nearing completion and his 
sesquicentennial is being celebrated in major exhibitions in 
morristown his longtime residence and landau germany his 
birthplace 
he was indisputably the father of american political 
cartooning he really defined the art form as we know it said 
richard samuel west author of a 1988 biography of cartoonist 
joseph keppler a nast contemporary 
west said nast transformed the droll genteel world of political 
cartooning that existed in pre1860 america 
nast came along and said this politician is like the devil 
he is evil he is stealing your money and it shocked people 
said west he was dogmatic he was angry and he cared deeply 
about what was happening in the country 
an example was nasts tammany tiger representing the new york 
political machine of tammany hall often seen attacking the values 
of american society 
draper hill an editorial cartoonist with the detroit news who 
is writing a nast biography said nasts style was influenced by 
german french and english cartooning such as using animals and 
shakespearean references and his own political convictions 
he had a sense of integrity and independence from editorial 
policy that was nonexistent at the time said hill 
nast left landau for new york at age 6 and was drawing 
illustrations for city publications by his late teens he launched 
his career in 1860 by covering the campaign of italian patriot 
guiseppe garibaldi for illustrated publications in london and 
paris 
he reached his peak in the 1870s drawing for harpers weekly 
the nations most widely read magazine his work was prodigious 
more than 8000 drawings for his career 
he turned new york city political power william marcy boss 
tweed into a metaphor for corruption often depicting him as a 
bulging sack of money 
he did generous portrayals of civil war hero ulysses s grant 
who credited nast with helping him win the presidency in 1868 
some people felt nast went too far in his attack on publisher 
horace greeley a 1872 candidate for president against grant 
nasts lengthy assault on the candidate included illustrations 
of greeley defiling lincoln and eating his own words one drawing 
showed greeleys white hat and coat on a pole stormtossed and 
labeled something that will blow over 
greeley lost overwhelmingly and died soon after the election 
there were claims that nast contributed mightily to the rigors of 
greeleys campaign according to hill 
jim borgman a nationally syndicated editorial cartoonist for 
the cincinnati enquirer said nast may have exercised too much 
power 
nast could paint the world the way he saw it and a lot of 
people did not have a counterbalance i dont want to have that 
kind of responsibility borgman said 
he added that cartoonists today often eschew backing a cause in 
favor of lampooning just about everything 
herb block a washington post cartoonist who favors the nast 
approach agrees 
a lot of cartoonists today are doing just a kind of a gag 
cartoon without having any policy angle block said 
he said one of his nastinspired drawings showed caspar 
weinberger former us defense secretary with a 640 toilet seat 
around his neck symbolizing waste in the military 
the biggest nast displays this year have been in landau and 
morristown where the macculloch hall museum has a large permanent 
collection on display 
the landau museum has more than 2000 harpers weeklies said 
nicole van aanholt organizer of nast exhibitions there she said 
another major exhibit is planned for bonn germany in december 
nearly a dozen nast political drawings also can be seen at the 
fraunces tavern museum in new york city through late january 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
</TEXT>
</DOC>

