<TEXT>
a judges order consolidating nearly 70000 
claims against eaglepicher industries inc is a first and by no 
means guaranteed step in resolving the nations biggest product 
liability problem legal experts say 
lawyers for victims said they will appeal the move by us 
district judge jack b weinstein which they claim would lead to a 
settlement that shortchanges workers suffering from lung cancer 
and other diseases 
attorneys for other companies with large asbestos liabilities 
plan to wait for the eaglepicher case to develop before seeking 
class action status and experts warned that eaglepichers claims 
represented just a fraction of a crowded legal docket 
it is unprecedented innovative and one way to attack the 
problem but it does not represent a solution said drew berry a 
newark nj lawyer who represents several defendant companies 
for instance one hitch in a global settlement is that nearly 
all of the 100000 asbestos claims clogging state and federal 
courts name several companies whose products were used at a work 
place 
therefore resolution of claims against eaglepicher would 
represent only partial settlement of a victims demands lawsuits 
would remain on court dockets until claims against all defendants 
were resolved 
nonetheless weinstein got an important legal boost tuesday when 
a federal bankruptcy judge in cincinnati dismissed a motion to 
throw eaglepicher into involuntary bankruptcy proceedings that 
could have suspended all action in the case 
the motion was a lastminute attempt by victims lawyers to stop 
weinstein from declaring the class action which consolidates all 
present and future claims against eaglepicher for settlement 
in addition to declaring the class weinstein suspended all 
asbestos litigation involving eaglepicher but ordered the company 
to begin paying 45 million to victims who already have settled 
their cases 
a proposed settlement plan calls for creating a trust estimated 
at 625 million over 20 years to pay eaglepicher claimants 
victims representatives complained it offers too little money few 
safeguards and allows the company to pay its bills but not settle 
claims 
under the plan asbestos victims are the last in line to 
receive awards for compensation for their illnesses and deaths 
said heather maurer executive director of the 18000member 
asbetos victims of america 
plaintiffs lawyers said they would challenge the class action in 
the 2nd us circuit court of appeals on numerous legal grounds 
they said weinstein lacked jurisdiction appointed lawyers unfit to 
represent their clients and supported a plan that would 
shortchange victims 
also unresolved is whether weinstein can usurp jurisidiction 
from cases now in state courts in addition no method of payment 
has been established which both victim and company lawyers would 
be likely to fight 
we believe the judge does not have the power to do what he is 
purporting to do said fred baron a dallas lawyer for several 
thousand victims who said attorneys would mount a frontal 
attack on weinsteins order 
the battle over eaglepicher could shape the future of what is 
by far the biggest product liability problem ever to confront the 
us legal system cases clog state and federal courts nationwide 
and new claims are being filed daily 
asbestos was used widely in insulation boilers automobile 
brake linings and other products illness from inhaling asbestos 
fibers often takes decades to appear and cases have been mounting 
since the early 1970s 
weinstein favors mass settlements to save the time enormous 
cost and damage to companies reputations in bankruptcy 
proceedings but he is charting new waters and some companies with 
large asbestos liabilities said they were not eager to plunge in 
were very interested in what the judge is doing we have some 
question about whether he can pull it off said john obrien 
associate general counsel of keene corp which is struggling to 
cope with about 70000 lawsuits stemming from insulation products 
made by a subsidiary for more than 50 years 
more than a dozen companies already have filed for bankruptcy 
court protection because of their asbestos liabilites including 
celotex corp and national gypsum co in the last six weeks 
to declare a class action companies must demonstrate their 
funds are so limited that they cannot meet claims and continue 
normal operations eaglepicher said it faces bankruptcy soon 
without a resolution 
