<TEXT>
cs first boston inc said wednesday its 
institutional and management shareholders had approved a 725 
million restructuring designed to reverse the investment firms 
sagging fortunes 
the plan calls for the sale of 300 million in equity by cs 
first boston to its swiss owner cs holding and the injection of 
425 million in cash in exchange for the bulk of a troubled loan 
portfolio 
after the restructuring cs holding will control about 60 
percent of the privately controlled investment bank up from 445 
percent first boston corp is the north american subsidiary of cs 
first boston 
in a statement cs first boston said the loan portion of the 
deal is expected to be completed on friday with the rest of the 
restructuring done by monday 
the depth of our commitment to cs first boston is clear and 
the strength of our investment banking affiliate is beyond 
question said cs holding chairman rainer gut 
first boston though has undergone a major shakeup in recent 
weeks to clean up its balance sheet and cut costs during a severe 
downturn in business on wall street the firm has been hurt largely 
by troubles in the junk bond merger and real estate markets 
as part of its overhaul several top first boston executives 
have resigned or been ousted in the last six weeks and the firm has 
been laying off about 200 employees in the last two months of the 
year 
the company said all of cs first bostons institutional 
shareholders and 94 percent of its management shareholders approved 
the restructuring 
the bailout by cs holding which owns the the swiss bank credit 
suisse is the second this year by the parent of an ailing wall 
street subsidiary american express co early this year injected 
13 billion into shearson lehman holdings inc and took the 
company private 
the first boston restructuring rids the firm of the majority of 
11 billion in temporary bridge loans made to corporate 
clients that the firm has been unable to sell because of the 
collapse of the junk bond market 
under the restructuring cs first boston is placing all its 
bridge loans except for those to campeau corps federated 
department stores subsidiary and to jerrico inc into a special 
limited partnership 
in exchange cs first boston will receive a stake in the 
partnership and the 425 million in cash the firm still will be 
exposed to 377 million in bridge loans 
additionally cs first boston is writing off 360 million in 
soured investments that is expected to reduce the firms 1990 
earnings first boston made just 11 million last year and 
reportedly has losses so far this year 
</TEXT>
