<TEXT>
cbs inc today announced an offer to buy back 2 
billion of its own stock and disclosed that it lost 55 million 
from its coverage of major league baseball this year 
the company also said its board has unanimously elected the 
company president and chief executive laurence a tisch for the 
additional post of chairman succeeding william s paley who died 
on oct 26 
the company said it would repurchase up to 105 million shares 
of its common stock at 190 per share a significant premium over 
recent prices 
cbs stock has been hit hard recently by the networks disclosure 
that it would report a loss for the fourth quarter and lower 
earnings in 1991 the loss would be its first for any quarter 
excluding a restated loss in the fourth quarter of 1986 cbs has 
been hit hard by losses on sports programming and weakening ad 
revenue 
as part of the buyback cbs said the paley estate which 
controls an 8 percent stake and loews corp the tischcontrolled 
company that holds a 249 percent interest in cbs would tender 
their shares 
a portion of their stakes would be repurchased but their 
relative holdings of cbs common stock would not change the estate 
has been negotiating with cbs to sell the shares to pay tax 
obligations 
the announcement boosted the price of cbs stock which was up 
425 a share to 17412 in midday trading on the new york stock 
exchange the stock recently traded below 160 a share 
this offer will provide cbs shareholders with the opportunity 
to receive a premium over recent market prices of cbs shares for a 
significant portion of their shares while retaining a substantial 
equity investment in the company tisch said in a statement 
tisch said that after the buyback cbs still will have 800 
million in cash and securities to finance currnt operations 
the statement also said that in light of the repurchase of 
shares and the outlook for 1991 cbs expected to reduce its common 
stock quarterly dividend below the currrent 110 a share 
cbs for the first time disclosed an aftertax operating loss of 
55 million for the 1990 fourth quarter and the year from its 
expensive contract for baseball programming the network was hurt 
by weak advertising and the cincinnati reds fourgame sweep over 
the oakland athletics 
cbs also said it would take a 115 million charge against 
fourthquarter earnings to pay for anticipated losses over the 
course of its fouryear 106 billion major league baseball 
contract 
cbs last month announced that it would lose money for the 
octoberdecember quarter estimates on its baseball losses for 1990 
had been reported at under 100 million the network earned 601 
million or 233 a share in the same 1989 period 
other factors cited by the network for the losses included lower 
advertising revenue because of the economic downturn increased 
news costs covering the middle east crisis and reduced demand for 
advertising at its television and radio stations 
the company last month also announced that it would cut payments 
to television network affiliates next year for carrying its 
programs by 20 percent a move expected to save the company about 
30 million in 1991 cbs also has laid off workers to cut costs 
cbs said the stock buyback offer would begin in the next several 
days and expire on jan 21 if the offer is fully subscribed cbs 
would buy back an equal percentage of the amount tendered by all 
stockholders 
</TEXT>
