<TEXT>
great western financial corp bowed 
out of the stagnant real estate brokerage business wednesday 
saying it would close its great western real estate subsidiary 
the shutdown combined with layoffs announced last month at the 
real estate company puts 1506 people out of work 241 staff 
members and 1265 real estate agents who had contracted to work for 
great western full time 
little effect was expected on the parent compnys financial 
statement according to great western financial whose biggest 
subsidiary is great western bank the nations secondlargest 
savings and loan 
the real estate company was a tiny fragment of great westerns 
business the beverly hillsbased parent company had 38 billion 
in revenues in 1989 the yorba lindabased realty subsidiary had 
just 50 million in gross sales commissions 
there has been a host of recent layoffs and cutbacks at real 
estate companies throughout california where the market has slowed 
drastically in the past year after several years of booming sales 
and soaring prices 
no attempt was made to find a buyer for the great western real 
estate unit spokesman steve hawkins said he said employees of 
some field offices had inquired about taking over those offices 
in november great western real estate laid off its newhome 
sales force in yorba linda 
great western financial is generally regarded as healthy but has 
had big losses recently on commercial real estate loans in the 
northeast 
great western said the real estate unit never consistently met 
profit objectives since it was acquired in 1983 hawkins described 
the closure as part of great westerns attempts to refocus on its 
core businesses of mortgage lending and retail banking 
hawkins said the company would complete all transactions in 
escrow before shutting down so that customers would not be 
affected 
</TEXT>
