<TEXT>
every year artisans from all over the northeast flock to the 
annual holiday crafts fair at columbia university in new york to 
sell their pottery jewelry quilts and clothing but this year 
the market for crafts like that for goods sold by more 
traditional retailers is in a slump 
cherry schacher has been selling patchwork goods at the fair for 
10 years but this year she sold more placemats and pillows than 
500 quilts 
it is off a bit she said of her sales but after having had 
a slow year ms schacher came into manhattan expecting business to 
be down from the robust sales she enjoyed at past fairs 
like many artisans ms schacher depends on her handiwork for a 
large portion of her income however she and her husband who live 
in upstate ballston spa ny also make their living by playing in 
a country band several nights a week the music business helps make 
up for a drop in crafts sales 
alan goldfarb a glassblower from burlington vt also expected 
his business to be down at the fair but he was pleasantly 
surprised 
goldfarbs goblets and glass fish range from 1250 to 350 in 
price and he came prepared with more lowerpriced than higherend 
pieces yet by the end of his three days at the fair goldfarb had 
his highest sales total ever for the new york show 
he also found that the new works he displayed sold very well 
we were taking a chance he said but if you follow 
your heart it works 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
equals 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
instead of buying christmas gifts for his family david ryan has 
been shopping for something else lately a job 
at 26 ryan is among the young adults coping with unemployment 
during the economic slump in massachusetts ryan lost his job at a 
boston investment firm several months ago and that means a holiday 
season without glitter 
my relatives have told me not to buy any gifts until after i 
get back to work ryan said its a little hard for me i would 
like to give some gifts to express my feelings about what they do 
for me during the year 
ryan has had to budget his money tightly he even is cutting 
back on greeting cards 
