<TEXT>
is this town big enough for two oil futures 
markets 
now that the persian gulf crisis has made crude oil a hot 
commodity the new york mercantile exchange may be in for some 
competition 
the neighboring commodity exchange which shares the same 
trading floor with the merc has discussed a deal with londons 
international petroleum exchange that could lead to crude oil 
trading on the comex officials said wednesday 
the mercantile exchange currently the worlds largest market 
for crude futures hasnt faced any competition in this country 
since the chicago board of trade gave up oil trading a few years 
ago 
oil experts say breaking into the oil market would be difficult 
for any newcomer 
there is a rule of thumb that only one contract in the same 
commodity would succeed in any given time zone said peter 
beutel an oil analyst with pegasus econometric group inc in 
hoboken nj 
the comex located with other new york futures exchanges in the 
world trade center in lower manhattan deals primarily in precious 
metals 
weve been considering agreements with many exchanges and now 
were talking with the ipe about joint trading benefits 
commodity exchange president david a halperin said in a statement 
a comex official who would speak only on condition of anonymity 
said crude futures were part of the discussions but the official 
was not sure what the plans entailed 
the official was not sure how soon an offering might be made 
assuming the comex and london can strike a deal a phone call 
placed to ipes new york office was not immediately returned 
crude oil has been the sexy futures contract in recent 
months since the iraqi invasion of kuwait in august sent oil 
prices swinging wildly said christian gohler an oil broker with 
merrill lynch energy futures the bustle of trading at the 
mercantile exchange oil pit has contrasted sharply with relatively 
weak demand for metals 
if the comex offered sweet crude oil contracts it would compete 
directly with the mercantile exchange but the comex might offer 
contracts in sour crude which could put it a step ahead of the 
mercantile exchange which is now considering a sour crude 
contract 
sweet crude has a low sulfur content and is most desirable for 
refining sour crude has more sulfur and is more difficult to 
refine 
the two new york futures markets have failed in past discussions 
to reach agreement on a merger ipe was also once talking with the 
mercantile exchange about a trading agreement but those talks fell 
through 
oil traders said the emergence of a crude contract on the 
commodity exchange could stir bad blood between the exchanges the 
mercantile exchange said it would not fear any competition 
we think were the best at what we do so were ready to take 
on any comers said robert r davis senior vice president at the 
mercantile exchange 
analysts who follow oil futures pricing doubt that the comex 
would be successful in offering a contract that competed with the 
mercantile exchanges light sweet crude futures 
generally there is just room for one market for each commodity 
because the big players tend to gravitate to the place where the 
volume is greatest and they can get the best deals beutel said 
at the time the mercantile exchange first offered its futures 
contracts for light sweet crude in 1983 the chicago board of trade 
began offering contracts for louisiana light sweet crude but those 
sales were soon abandoned traders said 
but beutel said an oil contract that could be traded in both 
london and new york would create advantages for the biggest oil 
trading companies that maintain offices in both cities 
the fact that you could enter a position in london and remove 
it in new york would come close to that 24hour trading that some 
people want he said it would put local traders and smaller 
companies at a disadvantage he said because they would have a 
harder time keeping abreast of trading for so many hours each day 
london oil traders can now deal in futures of brent blend a 
north sea oil oil futures are also available on the singapore 
international monetary exchange but its contracts for dubai crude 
oil are not widely traded analysts said 
