<TEXT>
the chicago mercantile exchange and the chicago 
board of trade said they would implement new maximum daily price 
limits on two stock index futures contracts starting thursday 
the daily limit on the sampp 500 futures contract at the merc will 
be narrowed from 30 points roughly equivalent to 250 points on 
the dow jones industrial average to 20 points equivalent to 
about 150 dow points the merc said wednesday 
the daily limit on the mmi futures contract at the board of 
trade will be narrowed from 50 points equivalent to about 250 dow 
points to 30 points equivalent to about 150 dow points the merc 
said 
all other price limits also known as circuit breakers remain 
at current levels the worlds two largest commodities exchanges 
said in a statement 
the commodity futures trading commission has approved the new 
price limits which were proposed by the governing boards of each 
exchange in september the statement said 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

