<DOCNO> AP901212-0269 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
dirk jan depree who founded herman miller 
inc and turned it into the secondlargest us office furniture 
company has died 
depree died monday night in a holland rest home at age 99 
depree founded zeelandbased herman miller in 1923 buying star 
furniture co with the help of his fatherinlaw for whom the new 
company was named depree served as general manager until 1949 and 
president until 1962 when he was named chairman 
the company is the second largest of its kind after steelcase 
inc of grand rapids 
depree a zeeland native was not a designer but the company 
became known for hiring nowfamous industry names such as gilbert 
rohde charles eames and robert probst 
herman miller furniture has been featured at the new york museum 
of modern art and the smithsonian institution 
during deprees tenure the company produced the house of 
tomorrow for the 1934 worlds fair the modular wall storage 
system molded plywood and plastic chairs of the 1940s and the 
stacking chairs of the 1950s 
earlier this year depree was named to the american national 
business hall of fame which recognized his development in the 
1950s of a humanistic approach to the work place including 
participatory management profit sharing and employee incentives 
the publicly held fortune 500 company has been named one of the 
10 most admired companies by the magazine 
depree served nearly 10 years as pastor of ventura baptist 
church in zeeland he also served as international president of the 
gideons society 
deprees son hugh is president emeritus of the company and 
another son max is chairman his other surviving children are 
merle schaap of lansing and betty van kley of zeeland 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

